spec: asyncio_extra128
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html — Python asyncio module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/locks.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 256 theme — asyncio.Condition class identity and method qualnames. NEW in extra128: asyncio.Condition.__name__=='Condition' (len=9); asyncio.Condition.__module__=='asyncio.locks'; asyncio.Condition.__bases__[0].__name__=='_ContextManagerMixin'; asyncio.Condition.__mro__.__len__()==4 (MRO=[Condition, _ContextManagerMixin, _LoopBoundMixin, object]); asyncio.Condition.notify.__qualname__=='Condition.notify' (len=16); asyncio.Condition.notify_all.__qualname__=='Condition.notify_all' (len=20); asyncio.Condition.wait.__qualname__=='Condition.wait' (len=14); asyncio.Condition.wait_for.__qualname__=='Condition.wait_for' (len=18); asyncio.Condition.__init__.__qualname__=='Condition.__init__' (len=18); asyncio.Condition.notify.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self, n); asyncio.Condition.notify_all.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); asyncio.Condition.wait.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); asyncio.Condition.wait_for.__code__.co_argcount==2; asyncio.Condition.__init__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self, lock). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "asyncio.Condition has no acquire or release methods. Unlike asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Condition does not expose acquire/release directly; it wraps an underlying Lock internally; condition variable access is via async with (using __aenter__/__aexit__ from _ContextManagerMixin) not acquire/release. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "asyncio.Condition.__mro__.__len__() == 4. MRO is [Condition, _ContextManagerMixin, _LoopBoundMixin, object]; same 4-element structure as asyncio.Lock and asyncio.Semaphore (covered in extra127). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "asyncio.Condition.notify_all.__qualname__.__len__() == 20. 'Condition.notify_all' is 20 chars: 'Condition.'=10 + 'notify_all'=10 = 20; the longest method qualname in this spec. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
